-### Minor patch to §3.2 (not overwriting, just noting for patcher)
-
-- **Three heuristics for formulating decisions** (line 6612): (1) set boundaries of the architectural space under consideration (Ch 11 System Problem Statement); (2) decisions must significantly influence metrics (low-sensitivity decisions should be dropped); (3) include only architectural decisions (not design decisions like launch-site location). Apollo example: 9 decisions retained from a longer initial list.
-- **Properties of architectural decisions and metrics** (Box 14.1, line 6891 — already cited): modeling breadth vs. depth, ambiguity, categorical-variable dominance, subjectivity, if-then objective functions, coupling/emergence.
-- **Simon's Design-Activity 4 layers** (line 6759): **representing** (encode problem), **structuring** (reason about structure — decision order, coupling), **simulating** (evaluate satisfaction of needs), **viewing** (present results human-readably). Existing §3.2 calls out "Four Tasks of Decision Support" — the same four.
